<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900815-0048</DOCNO><DOCID>900815-0048.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Air Products andamp; Chemicals Inc.:   Sale of Stake in Project   Brings Firm $6 Million Gain</HL><DATE>08/15/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   APD</CO><IN>TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><LP>   Air Products andamp; Chemicals Inc. said the sale of equity inan energy project will produce a one-time gain of $6 million,or 11 cents a share, in the fourth quarter ending Sept. 30.The company said this shouldn't affect analysts' consensusoperating earnings estimates of about $55 million, or $1 ashare, for the quarter and about $215 million, or $3.88 ashare, for the year.   Air Products, based in Allentown, Pa., said the gain willcome from the sale of a 50% equity interest in a $190 millioncogeneration plant under construction in Cambria County, Pa.The transaction to Energy Investors Fund LP of Boston, Mass.,is valued at $30 million, which will produce a $6 milliongain in the fourth quarter.</LP><TEXT>   The Cambria facility will burn waste coal to generateelectricity and steam that will be sold under 20-year supplycontracts. Air Products and its equity partners have invested$1.2 billion in six environmental and energy projects. Thesale of equity provides Air Products with additionalfinancing, accelerated cash flows and improved tax benefits.</TEXT></DOC>